;
Number 44
Name Chanatahe's Circle
REGION 200
FOREST
FIXED_LIGHT
*DESCRIPTION_START
Massive oak and maple trees circle this clearing, their canopies forming
a solid 'roof' save for a small opening over the center of the firepit.
Various rocks and trees have glowing sigils which pulse in tune with the
threads of power that converge here.  The sigils are arranged to be the
foci of the threads, so that virtually anything tried here can be achieved
if done right.  An unlit bonfire sits in the center of the clearing,
awaiting use.
*DESCRIPTION_END
;
Number 1403
Name Tavern
FIXED_LIGHT
INDOOR_FLOOR
CHANNEL 1403
REGION 200
*DESCRIPTION_START
Most of this area has been cleaned up, with the rubble removed and the
floor swept.  Overhead, the mug rack has the three intact mugs hanging
on it.  The bar has been repaired as much as possible, but the shelves
behind it are all empty.  Only one of the three brass taps on the wall
pours any beverage at all.
*DESCRIPTION_END
ITEM 0 204
ITEM 1 1312 LIT
ITEM 2 65 VAL2=1409 UNLOCKED
ITEM 3 65 VAL2=1404 UNLOCKED
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM READ 0
This room is always loaded in the game.  You are more than welcome (if not
encouraged) to come in any time to roleplay.  It is IMPERATIVE that you save
your character here, so when you leave, come here and EXIT, not disconnect.
I hope you enjoy yourselves here.

Note: If you don't have access to board 24 yet, email Druid for access.
If you have multiple accounts, specify which account gets access.
*DESCRIPTION_END
;
;
;
;
; POKE, Rank 2 or higher, BRIII                 2
; RUB,  Rank 3 or higher, Regen                 3
; CONC, Rank 4 or higher, (246)                 5
; PUSH, All ranks         Spectral Shield       1
; PULL, All ranks         BRI                   1
INumber 960
Name 318
WORN_DON
ARMOR
EQUAL ITEMADJ1 145
EQUAL ITEMADJ2 1130
IFPREVERB2 EXAM -1
        CLEARVERB
        ECHO PLAYER You sense the goodness of the power inhabiting the aura.
        IFVAR INTNUM3 = 1
                ECHO PLAYER **GM EYES ONLY**
                ECHO PLAYER This amulet is crafted for members of the Shemri Church only.
                ECHO PLAYER Set VAL5 to the rank of the member.  This is a number from one to five.
                ECHO PLAYER Cartin Greycloak and Jacqueline are the two people who are rank 5.
                ECHO PLAYER They alone can set ranks in the Church at this time.
                ECHO PLAYER As there is a ritual to both create amulets and promote people
                ECHO PLAYER There are few reasons for a GM to be asked for one.  Instead send them
                ECHO PLAYER to the temple elders.
        ENDIF
ENDIF
;              
NUMBER 242
NAME Church Street
FIXED_LIGHT
OUTDOOR_OTHER
*DESCRIPTION_START
A whitewashed wooden building houses the Church of Shemri. You can see its
quaint steeple for some distance. Within is a bell for announcing weddings
and other occasions. On the opposite side of the street, through a stone
arch, is a shrine to Amilor.   A wooden door, flower-decked, leads into
the Church of Shemri.
*DESCRIPTION_END
EXIT S 241
EXIT ABOVE 2152
ITEM 0 200 VAL2=333 CLOSED ; Shemri door
ITEM 1 420 ADJ1=312
ITEM 2 465 ADJ1=347 ADJ2=355
ITEM 3 60 VAL2=591
IFPREVERB GO 3 ; Amilor arch
	IFVAR ALIGN < 0
		CLEARVERB
		ECHO PLAYER You hear a voice in your mind, "Your presence is not desired here, dark one."
		ECHO OTHERS %n moves towards the arch, but is suddenly shoved to the ground!
		POSITION LAY
	ENDIF
	IFVAR ALIGN > -1
		ECHO PLAYER You hear a voice in your mind, "Come in peace, my friend."
	ENDIF
ENDIF
;
NUMBER 333
NAME Church of Shemri, narthex
REGION 205
ASTRAL
FIXED_LIGHT
*DESCRIPTION_START
The narthex, a sort of entry hall for the church, is painted white and
laboriously trimmed in blue scrollwork resembling nothing more than frothy
waves. Two tiled pillars rise into an archway leading into the church
proper and overhead is a model of the planets and the sun, showing Andor
to be in the center.
*DESCRIPTION_END
INDOOR_FLOOR
FIXED_LIGHT
EXIT O 242
IFPREVERB POINT -1
        IFVAR ARCHNUM = 163
                CLEARVERB
                ECHO PLAYER A young priestess takes the donation, bowing her thanks to you quickly.
                ECHO OTHERS A young priestess takes %n's donation, bowing her thanks.
                ADD SHEMCOPPER ITEMVAL1
                REMOVEITEM -1
        ENDIF
        IFVAR ARCHNUM = 162
                CLEARVERB
                ECHO PLAYER A young priestess takes the donation, bowing her thanks to you.
                ECHO OTHERS A young priestess takes %n's donation, bowing her thanks.
                ADD SHEMSILVER ITEMVAL1
                REMOVEITEM -1
        ENDIF
        IFVAR ARCHNUM = 161
                CLEARVERB
                ECHO PLAYER A young priestess takes the donation, bowing her profuse thanks to you.
                ECHO OTHERS A young priestess takes %n's donation, bowing her profuse thanks.
                ADD SHEMGOLD ITEMVAL1
                REMOVEITEM -1
        ENDIF
        IFVAR SHEMCOPPER > 10
                EQUAL FLAG4 SHEMCOPPER
                DIV FLAG4 10
                ADD SHEMSILVER FLAG4
                MOD SHEMCOPPER 10
        ENDIF
        IFVAR SHEMSILVER > 10
                EQUAL FLAG4 SHEMSILVER
                DIV FLAG4 10
                ADD SHEMGOLD FLAG4
                MOD SHEMSILVER 10
        ENDIF
        IFVAR SHEMGOLD > 0
                ADD PVAL86 SHEMGOLD
                EQUAL SHEMGOLD 0
        ENDIF
        IFVAR PVAL86 > 5000
                SUB PVAL86 5000
                ADD PVAL87 5
        ENDIF
ENDIF
